---
import TradeHubLayout from '../layouts/TradeHubLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How does the AI handle drainage emergencies?",
    answer: "Drainage emergencies are nasty, urgent, and time-sensitive — blocked sewers, backed-up toilets, flooding from drain collapses. The AI is trained to recognise these situations and escalate them immediately. If a caller describes sewage coming up through manholes, water flooding into their property, or a complete drainage failure, it flags the call as critical and contacts you directly. Routine unblocking requests and CCTV survey enquiries are captured and sent to you for normal follow-up."
  },
  {
    question: "Most drainage work is reactive — customers don't plan it. Does the AI handle that?",
    answer: "Exactly right, and that's precisely why this service matters for drainage engineers. Nobody wakes up thinking 'I'll book a drain unblocking today.' They call when there's a problem — and they call now, not later. If you're already on site jetting a sewer line, you can't answer. Rapid Receptionist catches those reactive calls instantly, captures the problem details, and makes sure you don't lose the work to the next drainage company that picks up."
  },
  {
    question: "Can the AI understand the difference between a simple blockage and a collapsed drain?",
    answer: "The AI asks targeted questions to help you assess what you're walking into — is this a single blocked toilet or multiple drains backing up? Is there flooding? How long has the problem been going on? Has this happened before? It captures the symptoms so you can gauge whether it's a straightforward rodding job or something that might need CCTV and excavation. It won't diagnose the problem — that's your expertise — but it gives you the information to prioritise your response."
  },
  {
    question: "I offer CCTV drain surveys — can the AI handle those enquiries?",
    answer: "Yes. CCTV survey enquiries often come from homebuyers, conveyancing solicitors, or property developers who need pre-purchase or pre-build surveys. The AI captures the essential details: property type, reason for the survey, timeline, and location. These are often high-value leads because they frequently uncover work that needs doing. The AI makes sure every one of them reaches you with enough detail to quote quickly."
  },
  {
    question: "A lot of my emergency work comes through insurance companies. How does that work?",
    answer: "Insurance-referred emergency work is time-critical — the insurer expects rapid response, and delays cost you the contract. When an insurance company or loss adjuster calls, the AI captures the claim reference, the property details, and the nature of the drainage emergency. It treats these as high-priority calls because they often are. You get the details immediately so you can respond within the insurer's SLA window."
  },
  {
    question: "Drainage work is messy — I can't always check my phone. How do I get leads?",
    answer: "We get it — you're not checking your phone when you're waist-deep in a manhole. Every lead captured by the AI is sent to you immediately via SMS, email, or through the Rapid Receptionist dashboard. When you surface and check your phone, everything's there — customer name, number, location, job description, urgency level. You can batch your callbacks between jobs without worrying about what you might have missed."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you understand the difference between domestic and commercial drainage?",
    answer: "Yes. We configure the AI to handle both domestic and commercial drainage enquiries. A homeowner with a blocked kitchen sink needs different information captured than a facilities manager reporting drain problems across a retail park. A property developer needing soakaway calculations and drainage design for a new build needs a different level of detail again. The AI adapts its questions to the type of enquiry."
  },
  {
    question: "What about tanker and jetting work — high-value commercial contracts?",
    answer: "Commercial tanker and jetting contracts are some of the highest-value work in drainage. When a business or local authority calls about interceptor cleaning, tanker emptying, or high-pressure jetting for commercial drainage systems, the AI captures the scope, location, access details, and timeframe. These leads often run into thousands of pounds per job, so missing even one call can cost you significantly. Rapid Receptionist makes sure that never happens."
  }
];
